author: Ronan McGreevy
title: Quiet ferries suggest holidaymakers have heeded lockdown warnings
description: Evidence from Dublin Port indicate British visitors are staying away
content:
Holy Thursday is traditionally one of the busiest days at Dublin Port as British holidaymakers avail of the long Easter weekend to travel to Ireland. The evidence this year, however, is that people are heeding the public health advice and staying at home.
